SELECT
    MRM.GMPI_ID,
    COUNT(DISTINCT OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) AS SUBSCRIBER_COUNT
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.OM_MEMBER_TOTAL OMT
JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH MRM
    ON MRM.GMPI_ID = OMT.GMPI_ID
WHERE OMT.CODE = 'BCS'
  AND OMT.REPORT_MONTH BETWEEN '2025-01-01' AND '2026-01-01'
  AND OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY MRM.GMPI_ID
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) > 1
ORDER BY SUBSCRIBER_COUNT DESC;
This gives you:
GMPI_ID	SUBSCRIBER_COUNT
123456	3
987654	2
That means GMPI_ID 123456 has 3 different eligible insurance company IDs.
To see the actual subscriber IDs for those members, use:
WITH MULTIPLE_SUBSCRIBERS AS
(
    SELECT
        OMT.GMPI_ID
    FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.OM_MEMBER_TOTAL OMT
    WHERE OMT.CODE = 'BCS'
      AND OMT.REPORT_MONTH BETWEEN '2025-01-01' AND '2026-01-01'
      AND OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY OMT.GMPI_ID
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) > 1
)

SELECT DISTINCT
    OMT.GMPI_ID,
    OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID,
    OMT.REPORT_MONTH
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.OM_MEMBER_TOTAL OMT
JOIN MULTIPLE_SUBSCRIBERS MS
    ON OMT.GMPI_ID = MS.GMPI_ID
WHERE OMT.CODE = 'BCS'
  AND OMT.REPORT_MONTH BETWEEN '2025-01-01' AND '2026-01-01'
ORDER BY
    OMT.GMPI_ID,
    OMT.MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID,
    OMT.REPORT_MONTH;
One important correction: based on your screenshot, both GMPI_ID and MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID appear to come from OM_MEMBER_TOTAL. If that is correct, you may not need MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH at all. The simplest version would be:
SELECT
    GMPI_ID,
    COUNT(DISTINCT MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) AS SUBSCRIBER_COUNT
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.OM_MEMBER_TOTAL
WHERE CODE = 'BCS'
  AND REPORT_MONTH BETWEEN '2025-01-01' AND '2026-01-01'
  AND MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY GMPI_ID
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) > 1
ORDER BY SUBSCRIBER_COUNT DESC;
The key line is:
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT MBR_ELIG_INSURANCE_COMPANY_ID) > 1
It means: only show GMPI IDs connected to more than one unique subscriber/insurance company ID
